				\begin{document}$$_4$$\end{document} emissions. LMDs provide a non-invasive and efficient method for evaluating the impact of dietary strategies on the greenhouse gas emissions of livestock. The work in12 examines LMDs as instruments for quantifying methane emissions in ruminants such as sheep, goats, and cattle. This review addresses several aspects of LMDs, including measurement protocols and data analysis techniques. The author also highlights limitations such as its lower accuracy compared to other methods and the labor-intensive nature of the measurements. On the other hand, Zheng et al.13 propose a method for predicting CH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
