				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\copyright$$\end{document} sensor used to measure methane concentrations is between 500 and 10,000 ppm. Therefore, any increase below 500 ppm is consider noise, as the reading from the sensor is inaccurate at this point.

